# Architecture

- **Server actions**: No business logic. Only call `onServerAction` and then one or more service methods. See `src/app/actions/user-actions.ts`.
- **API route handlers**: No business logic. Use `withApiContext` and delegate to services. See `src/app/api/health/route.ts`.
- **Services**: All business logic lives in `src/lib/services/`. Services depend on `RequestContext` and repositories; they do not call `getCloudflareContext()` or use raw D1.
- **Persistence**: Only in `src/lib/repositories/` (D1). Repositories receive the DB (from context) in the constructor; no Cloudflare env in repository methods.
- **Frontend state management**: Default to reducer-driven state with `@eetr/react-reducer-utils` (action types, state, reducer, `bootstrapProvider`, Provider + hook) across pages and complex components. Use `useState` only for simple local state in simple components. No ad-hoc global state outside this pattern. See `src/context/admin-state.ts`.
- **Icons**: Use `lucide-react` only; import named icons (e.g. `import { IconName } from "lucide-react"`); do not add other icon libraries.
- **Where to add code**: New features add services/repos; entry points (actions, API routes) only wire context and call services; new client state domains add reducer modules under `src/context/` or `src/store/`.
- **Password hashing**: `src/lib/auth/password-hash.ts` uses Web Crypto PBKDF2 for new hashes (Workers-safe). Legacy Argon2id PHC strings use the **argon-hasher** Worker (`ARGON_HASHER` → `POST /verify`) when the binding exists; if `/verify` fails, login fails (no MD5 fallback). If the binding is missing (e.g. local dev), Argon2 rows fall back to legacy **MD5 hex** only for 32-char MD5 accounts. Configure `wrangler.jsonc` with `service: "argon-hasher"` and matching `props` (e.g. `internal: true`) per the hasher project. Do not add native Node addons in the app bundle.
